{
  "texts": [
    "It appears the semantic component is more dominant for IMDb and Yelp compared to Amazon.",
    "One possible reason is that the length of texts is shorter for Amazon compared to the other datasets (see the data statistics in Table 2).",
    "Hence, longer texts have a greater opportunity to reinforce sentiment being expressed, which makes it more robust to different linguistic realizations.",
    "Appendix E.2 further explores this hypothesis by considering additional sentiment classification datasets.",
    "Section 6.1 demonstrated that the linguistic realization of the context in multiple-choice reading comprehension has measurable influence on the output distribution over the options."
  ]
}